==English==
===Etymology===
After the East Germanic tribe of the [[w:Vandals|Vandals]], which looted Rome in 455.

===Noun===
'''vandalism''' (''uncountable'')

#[[needless|Needless]] [[damage]] or [[destruction]] of [[property]], usually someone else's property or common or shared property.
#Damage to an online [[encyclopedia]] or [[dictionary]] by the insertion of false information.
====Synonyms====
*[[vandalization]]

====Related terms====
*[[vandal]]
*[[vandalise]], [[vandalize]]

